title: 'DONT WASTE YOUR MONEY. GET SUGAR'
body: I've been using it since a month, and had to stop- not because it dried up but because the applicator is the worst. It removes the eyeliner more than it applies. The tip is always dry regardless of how much ink/colour is still left in the liner. You'll have to slant it and apply from the inner edges of the tip. It's a TASK! Just get the SUGAR eyeliner which comes around Rs.420ish rather. Sugar hasnt disappointed me yet.

title: 'Best'
body: Slightly pricy other than that it's the best

title: 'Not great'
body: The quality should reflect in price. My frame of reference is Maybelline Tattoo liner, which is a great eyeliner. This is uncomfortable to use, doesn't stay on for long and God forbid if you sweat, the tip is not pigmented you have to swipe multiple times to get any colour. The tip is also very thick, making it impossible to do much besides a thick line. I wouldn't buy it again.

title: 'Not meet my expectations'
body: It's like very thin line.... No liquid inside very dry form not much black color.. Don't buy for this price range it is utterly waste
